subtitle 240 And we're off!
subtitle 650 Super Mario Bros. "AISSON" by Levi Clayton
subtitle 1400 Abillity to run through walls allows us to do that flagpole glitch
subtitle 2400 It can also make some levels easier, and saves many frames
subtitle 2800 That wall clip is the easiest humanly possible method
subtitle 3455 Here, we clip into the wall so when we drop we end up in a pipe (literally)
subtitle 3700 with left+right to slow down instantly, we've saved two framerules over the normal speedrun
subtitle 4700 At the end of this level, you'll see the FPG again
subtitle 5408 I find it easier to jump to the fifth stair, then drop
subtitle 5650 But this is a TAS, not me
subtitle 6000 The "Fast 4-2" framerule is easy to save here
subtitle 6257 Because we can clip through walls by walking into them
subtitle 7200 We should be about four framerules ahead of the any% speedrun now
subtitle 7400 Clipping through the top stair allows us to drop straight into the pipe, like in 1-2
subtitle 7950 Did you hate 8-1 as a kid? Well look no further!
subtitle 8150 Return of the floor clip!
subtitle 8826 Hitting the star block despite it being completely moot
subtitle 9500 Anyway, this seems trivial. You can read some donations if you like.
subtitle 10000 The 10000 frame barrier and we've got an FPG done!
subtitle 10800 Heard you like BBG. Well we can do that too! Minus the bullet bill.
subtitle 11585 Save time here by not needing to slow down
subtitle 11990 Intentionally slow down to avoid fireworks
subtitle 12640 Hammer Brothers! No problem for us clipping and all that.
subtitle 14626 The last level of the game.
subtitle 15520 This wall jump is frame perfect, just like the normal one.
subtitle 15875 Wrong warp!
subtitle 16200 Backwards swimming achieved by holding Left+Right, although it's possible in real life
subtitle 16420 by swimming at full speed, tapping left and not holding any direction. It's not as broken.
subtitle 17030 The game's almost over now.
subtitle 17245 Cut!
